To achieve a fade-in transition when navigating to a new route in Flutter, you can use the `PageRouteBuilder` widget. Here's an example of how you can do it:

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

class FadeRouteTransition extends PageRouteBuilder {
  final Widget page;

  FadeRouteTransition({required this.page})
      : super(
          pageBuilder: (context, animation1, animation2) => page,
          transitionDuration: const Duration(milliseconds: 500),
          transitionsBuilder: (context, animation1, animation2, child) {
            return FadeTransition(
              opacity: animation1,
              child: child,
            );
          },
        );
}
```

You can then use this `FadeRouteTransition` class to navigate to a new route like this:

```dart
Navigator.of(context).push(
  FadeRouteTransition(
    page: YourNewPage(),
  ),
);
```

In this example, `YourNewPage` is the new page you want to navigate to. The `FadeRouteTransition` class will handle the fade-in transition when navigating to this page.

You can customize the transition duration by changing the value of `transitionDuration` in the `FadeRouteTransition` class.

